args: O creature small of stature, become my\nlimbs and move with my will! Onmyo!
Their hideout is probably located here\nin the deep woods, so go look around and\nsee if there are any caves or structures.
Ya never cease to amaze, Lord Seimei!\nMakin' ten critters into shikigami at the\nsame time is right impressive!
Look here. It seems one of the birds\nhas already returned.
...Ah, I see. It found a cabin that looks like\nit would make a perfect hiding place for\npeople. Please, lead the way.
Hoo-eee! That's more suspicious than\na pile'a corn by the side'a the road!\nIt's gotta be the hideout!
Hide, you stupid fox! There are people\ncoming out of the cabin!
*gulp* He's the one what killed yer\ngrandpappy with a curse, ain't he?\nThe one who practices fell onmyodo!
I dunno what kinda technique he was just\nusin', but I reckon it was real nasty.
No, it's just a barrier—though likely an\nirritatingly powerful one.
Tch. This isn't going to be easy, but\nwe have no choice but to break through it.
Astounding, Lord Seimei! You brought\nDoman's barrier down in an instant!
Ya went and played us for a couple'a right\nfools, master! We were thinkin' it'd take all\nday and a night what to bring that down!
C'mon, Lord Seimei! Don't just ignore us\nlike that! It ain't right!
Well, heck. He's even poutier than usual.\nA chicken's gonna walk all over that lip\nif he ain't careful.
Mayhap bein' this close to his revenge\nis makin' his mind go all screwy.
Doubtful. Lord Seimei is nothing if not\ncool and collected in a crisis.
Let's just get after him for now. It's far\ntoo dangerous for him to be storming\nDoman's hideout all by himself.
Right ya are. Lord Seimei! Wait uuup!
Lord Seimei, are you all right?!
Of course I am. Look around you—\nthis base is filled with pathetic nobodies.
And you made a right mess of 'em!
Why, if it isn't my old friend Seimei!\nWelcome! I'll have to prepare a suitable\nreception for you post-haste.
Escort him to the next life, my shikigami!
Save the nonsense for your sleep-talk,\nstupid fox; the real terrors here are not\nhis shikigami...
Well, heck! That was a whole lotta buildup\nfor a whole lotta bull plop.
Think about it, you stupid fox—the reason\nour foe seemed pathetic and weak was\nbecause he WAS pathetic and weak.
It's just some chump. It's laughable that\nhe thought he could play the role of\nDoman with a display like that.
Cow cuds! This Doman here was just\na Mukuroshu in disguise?!
A body double, hm.\nDid you know right away, Lord Seimei?
I knew the moment I examined the barrier\naround the cabin.
It was sloppy work, far beneath Doman.
Where ya headin' now, Lord Seimei?

Do you have to ask? I'm going to help
the villagers the Mukuroshu abducted.
They must be holding them somewhere
inside this structure.
Hot dang! I'm gonna help, too!
Are you all right, little one? ...Ah!\nLord Seimei? What's going on?
Her mana is weak. Doman must have\nleeched it out with his fell onmyodo.
Had she been his victim much longer,\nher life would likely have been forfeit.\nHowever, she should recover now.
What fortune! In that case, have this candy.\nThere's nothing better for getting your\nstrength back than some sweets!
Suckin' out somebody's mana?\nThat Doman is a right nasty piece'a work,\nI tell ya what!
I have to wonder why he came all the way\nto this new land just to perform such a\nvile and heinous act.
His reason for coming here lies elsewhere.\nIf all he wanted was to suck the mana out\nof people, he could've done it in Hinomoto.
This was likely just a way to sate his own\nmorbid curiosity, or perhaps a method of\ndeveloping his fell onmyodo further.

His ultimate goal is to revitalize the mana
from a dragon-vein spring, open a door to
the other world—the Realm of the Dead—
and acquire the Yomi chi held within.
And there might just be such a spring\nconveniently located in Alberia...
I overhead the man you called Doman\nearlier. He said something about heading\nwest toward the dragon-vein spring.
And when he left, he took our mayor\nwith him to act as a guide!
Please, you have to rescue him!
We gots to hurry, Lord Seimei!
You don't need to tell me that. Come on.
